CatDescriptText: Mr. Leo Yates, 183 Shetland Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1958, pg.2 with question: "Do people, whom you know, place more emphasis on social life than civic responsibilities?" answer reads: "I think that the persons in my age group, and I'm 22 years of age, stress more emphasis on the social rather than community responsibilities."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Leo Yates, wearing eyeglasses, tweed cap, and dark varsity-style jacket with snaps, collar, and White Hawk patch with Native American profile, standing in front of marble wall with decorative trim, left store window displaying tobacco products
